record_data.record_plain_text: ?EXHIBIT B DESCRIPTION OF CO-OWNERS’ PROJECTS Soldier Creek The Project is located in Nemaha County, Kansas. It will consist of one hundred and twenty (120) GE wind turbines, of which fifty-eight (58) are 2.72 MW, three (3) are 2.52 MW, and fifty-nine (59) are 2.3 MW, for a total generating nameplate of 301.02 MW. Irish Creek The Project is located in Marshall County, Kansas. It is expected to consist of one hundred fifty-one (151) GE 2.0 MW wind turbine generators for a total generating nameplate of 302 MW, but the turbine configuration may be revised when the project is constructed. High Banks The Project is located in Marshall County, Kansas. It is expected to consist of two hundred and thirty three (233) wind turbines, of which two hundred and five (205) are 2.82 MW, twenty-four (24) are 2.32 MW, and four (4) are 2.52 MW for a total generating nameplate capacity of 648 MW.

?EXHIBIT C
LINE LOSS METHODOLOGY
The losses are allocated on an incremental basis with Soldier Creek having priority. Losses increase incrementally from High Banks to Irish Creek to Soldier Creek. The approach is that each subsequent project is responsible for the incremental losses that it imposes on that line.

SECOND AMENDED SHARED INTERCONNECTION FACILITIES CO-OWNERS AGREEMENT This Second Amended Shared Interconnection Facilities Co-owners Agreement (this “Agreement”) is made as of June 25, 2024, by and between SOLDIER CREEK WIND, LLC (“Soldier Creek”), IRISH CREEK WIND, LLC (“Irish Creek”), and HIGH BANKS WIND, LLC (“High Banks”). Soldier Creek, Irish Creek, and High Banks are sometimes referred to in this Agreement individually as a “Co-Owner” or “Party”, and collectively as the “Co-Owners” or “Parties”. RECITALS WHEREAS Soldier Creek owns, operates, and maintains an approximately 301 MW wind generating facility located in Nemaha County, Kansas (“Soldier Creek Project”); WHEREAS Irish Creek owns, operates, and maintains an approximately 302 MW wind generating facility located in Marshal County, Kansas (“Irish Creek Project”); WHEREAS High Banks is developing and constructing, and will own, operate, and maintain, an approximately 648 MW wind generating facility located in Marshall County, (“High Banks Project”); WHEREAS as of the date hereof, each of Soldier Creek, Irish Creek, and High Banks are the beneficial owners, as tenants in common, of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, as described herein; and WHEREAS the parties intend to hold their respective interests and to provide for their mutual understanding as tenants in common with respect to the ownership, operation, development, financing and holding of the Shared Interconnection Facilities pursuant to and in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. NOW, THEREFORE in consideration of the premises and the mutual covenants, undertakings and conditions set forth below, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 DEFINITIONS 1.1 Definitions In this Agreement, unless there is something in the subject matter or context inconsistent therewith: submitted or created in the course of resolution of a dispute, including any information or data created by the arbitrators, and any award or other determination. Confidential Information excludes particular information that the receiving Co-owner(s) can establish with demonstrable written evidence is or was, through no wrongful act or omission of the Co-owner(s) making the disclosure: (d) at the time of disclosure generally available to the public; (e) prior to the time of acquisition in connection with the Shared Interconnection Facilities or either Project by the receiving Co-owner(s) or any of its Affiliates, already in the possession of or known to the receiving Co-owner(s) or any of its Affiliates on a lawful basis; (f) acquired from a Third Party who has, to the receiving Co-owner’s knowledge after due inquiry, lawful authority to disclose the applicable Confidential Information; or (g) independently developed by or for the receiving Co-owner(s) or an Affiliate of the receiving Co-owner(s) without the use or exploitation of Confidential Information. (e) such party shall take any corporate action to authorize any of the actions described in this definition; (f) any cause or proceeding against any such party shall be instituted in any court of competent jurisdiction seeking in respect of any such party, an adjudication in bankruptcy, reorganization, dissolution, winding up, liquidation, a composition or arrangement with creditors, a readjustment of debts, the appointment of a trustee, receiver, liquidator or the like of any such party or of all or any substantial part of its assets, or any other like relief in respect of any such party under any bankruptcy or insolvency law and: (i) such cause, proceeding or other action results in an entry of an order for relief or any such adjudication or appointment unless such order, adjudication or appointment is stayed or otherwise effectively reversed within 30 days thereof; or (ii) if such cause, proceeding or other action is being contested by any such party, as applicable, in good faith, the same shall continue undismissed, or unstayed and in effect, for any period of sixty (60) consecutive days; or (g) all or any material part of the assets of any such Party are attached, executed or sequestered upon or become subject to any order of a court or other process and such attachment, execution or sequestration order or process any such Party, and such Party shall not discharge the same or provide for its discharge in accordance with its terms, or procure a stay of execution thereof. “Financing” has the meaning set out in Section 0. “Force Majeure” has the meaning set out in Section 0. “Governmental Authority” and “Governmental Authorities” means, in relation to any Person, transaction, event, the Shared Interconnection Facilities or either Co-owner’s Project, any government, regulatory authority, governmental department, agency, commission, bureau, official, minister, ministry, organization, Crown corporation, court, board, tribunal, dispute settlement panel or body or other law, rule or regulation-making party: (i) having or purporting to have jurisdiction on behalf of any nation, province, state or other geographic or political subdivision thereof over such Person, transaction, event, the Shared Interconnection Facilities or either Co-owner’s Project; or (ii) exercising or entitled or purporting to exercise any administrative, executive, judicial, legislative, policy, regulatory or taxing authority or power over such Person, transaction, event, the Shared Interconnection Facilities or either Co-owner’s Project. “hereof”, “herein”, “herewith”, “hereto” and similar expressions mean and refer to this Agreement and, where relevant, to any particular Article, Section or Subsection hereof. “Indemnified Coowner” has the meaning set out in Section 0 hereof. “Indemnifying Coowner” has the meaning set out in Section 0 hereof. “Interconnection Agreement” means the generator interconnection agreement that each Co-owner has with Southwest Power Pool, Inc. and Evergy Kansas Central, Inc.
“Laws” means any laws, rules, statutes, regulations, codes, requirements and/or ordinances enacted, imposed or enforced by any Governmental Authorities that are applicable to and/or affect all or any part of the operation, maintenance or use of the Shared Interconnection Facilities. “Lender” means, collectively, each non-Affiliate Person including, without limitation, one or more banks, trust companies, life insurance companies and pension funds, providing Financing and any trustee or agent acting on any such non-Affiliate Person’s behalf and their successors and assigns. “Liabilities” has the meaning set out in Section 0. “NextEra” means NextEra Energy Resources, LLC. “Non-advancing Coowner” has the meaning set out in Section 0 hereof. “Notice” has the meaning set out in Section 0 hereof. “Operating Expenses” means Reimbursable Costs and the Operating Fee (each as defined in the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement). “Operator” means NextEra Energy Operating Services, LLC, or its designee, which shall be the initial operator of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, designated in the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement, and any other successor entity operating the Shared Interconnection Facilities, which shall be responsible for the operation and maintenance of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, as These agreements will include but not be limited to the agreements with government funding agencies, with Persons providing tangible equipment or services for the Shared Interconnection Facilities, and with any applicable power purchaser. “Total Transmission Loss” means, for any period, the total Energy loss along the Shared Interconnection Facilities, measured as the difference between the total Energy generated by the Projects during such period, and the total Energy delivered to the Westar Electric Buffalo Flats Switching Station during such period, as measured in (i) megawatt hours or (ii) as a percentage of the total Energy generated by the Projects during such period. ARTICLE 2 TERM 2.1 Term This Agreement shall come into force and effect as of the date of this Agreement and, except as otherwise provided, shall terminate upon the earliest to occur of: (a) the written agreement of all Coowners; and (b) one Coowner becoming the owner of the entire Shared Interconnection Facilities. All benefits and obligations of the parties which expressly or by their nature survive termination of this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect subsequent to and notwithstanding termination of this Agreement until they are fully satisfied or by their nature expire. No party shall by reason of termination of this Agreement be relieved of any obligation or liability towards any other party accrued under this Agreement before termination, and all those obligations and liabilities shall remain enforceable until they are fully satisfied or by their nature expire. ARTICLE 3 RELATIONSHIP AMONG COOWNERS 3.1 Ownership of the Shared Interconnection Facilities; Capacity The Shared Interconnection Facilities shall be held by the Coowners as tenants in common and not as joint tenants, the Coowners having as of the date of this Agreement the following respective undivided Coowner’s Interests in the Shared Interconnection Facilities: Segment A – 75-mile gen-tie from Soldier Creek Substation to POI (Stranger Creek) and related Soldier Creek substation equipment, including Series Capacitor Name of Co-Owner Co-Owner’s Interest Soldier Creek 25% Irish Creek 25% High Banks 50%
Segment B – 25-mile gen-tie from Irish Creek Substation to Soldier Creek Substation and related Irish Creek substation equipment Name of Co-Owner Co-Owner’s Interest Irish Creek 33% High Banks 67%
Each Co-owner has capacity commensurate with its ownership interest and uses such capacity to transmit Energy from its Project to the point of interconnection set forth in its Interconnection Agreement.
3.2 Disclaimer Of Partnership Each Coowner expressly disclaims any intention to create a partnership or joint venture. Each Coowner covenants with the other Coowner that it will not, at any time, allege or claim that a relationship of partnership, joint venture or (except as expressly provided in this Agreement) agency was or is created. Nothing in this Agreement shall constitute the Coowners to be partners or joint venturers or (except as expressly provided in this Agreement) constitute one to be the agent of another. Each Coowner expressly declares its intention to rely upon: (a) the relevant provisions, if any, of any legislation governing partnerships in the State of Kansas in which the Shared Interconnection Facilities are located, as amended from time to time, to the effect, inter alia, that joint tenancy, tenancy in common, joint property, common property or part ownership does not of itself create a partnership as to anything so held or owned, whether the tenants or owners do or do not share profits made by the use of it; and (b) the statutory and common law as it applies to tenants in common, save only to the extent that the same is, by the express provisions of this Agreement, amended or varied. For greater certainty, no Coowner shall have any authority to act for or on behalf of any other Co-owner or the other Coowners. 3.3 Several Liability Unless Approved by the Coowners, this Agreement and every instrument creating obligations of the Coowners to Third Parties and to each other in respect of the Shared Interconnection Facilities (other than any instrument entered into by a Coowner in its separate capacity as contemplated in this Agreement) shall, to the greatest extent possible, operate such that and contain provisions to the effect that: (a) only each Coowner’s Interest in the Shared Interconnection Facilities shall be bound thereby and the obligations thereunder are not otherwise binding upon nor shall resort be had to any other property of a Coowner; and (b) the rights and obligations of each Coowner thereunder shall be several and not either joint or joint and several and shall be limited to such Coowner’s Proportion of the aggregate liability in respect thereof. 3.4 Conduct of Business 3.4.1 In view of the exclusive and limited purposes of this Agreement, but subject to and without derogating from the benefits to and obligations of the respective Coowners and their respective Affiliates under the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement, nothing herein shall be deemed to restrict in any way the freedom of any Coowner or any Affiliate of a Coowner to conduct any business or activity whatsoever (including the acquisition, development, leasing, sale, operation and management of any electricity generation or transmission project) without any accountability to any other Coowner. Each Coowner shall have the absolute right to engage in any other businesses and other ventures for its own individual profit. No Coowner shall, by entering into this Agreement, acquire or be deemed to have acquired or become entitled to any interest in any other property owned by any other Coowner or in any other business or venture engaged in by the other Coowners (whether or not similar to the operation of the Shared Interconnection Facilities). It is the intent of the Co-owners that the provisions contained in this Agreement and in the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement shall not cause the Co-Owners (or any Co-Owner individually) to fail to be eligible for the waiver provided in 18 CFR §§ 35.28(d)(2) under FERC regulations. 3.5 Use of the Shared Interconnection Facilities The Coowners confirm that they shall not carry on any activity or business in connection with the Shared Interconnection Facilities other than as contemplated herein or as Approved by the Coowners. 3.6 Waiver of Partition and Sale The Coowners covenant and agree not to make application to any court under any legislation or pursuant to common law for the termination of the co-ownership of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, the intention being that the provisions of this Agreement shall govern the relationship of the Coowners with respect to the Shared Interconnection Facilities. 3.7 Permitted Encumbrances The Co-owners agree that notwithstanding anything contained herein except for the last sentence of this Section 0, (a) each of them is bound by and will comply with the Permitted Encumbrances and that in exercising their rights and performing their obligations hereunder and in respect of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, they shall abide by the provisions of the Permitted Encumbrances and not do, or omit to do, or cause or require any other party to do or omit to do anything that would constitute, or with the passage of time would result in, a default or breach under the terms of any Permitted Encumbrances, and (b) to the extent that any provisions of this Agreement constitute, or with the passage of time would result in, a default or breach under the provisions of any Permitted Encumbrance, the parties hereto agree that this Agreement is deemed to be amended to the extent necessary to rectify such default or breach, and the Co-owners agree to confirm such amendments in writing within 15 days after request by any Co-owner. With the Approval of all Co-owners, the Co-owners may elect to exempt any Permitted Encumbrance from the application of this Section 0. 3.8 Third Party Consents and Approvals The Co-owners agree that, notwithstanding anything contained herein, their exercise of any of their rights under this Agreement shall be subject to and conditional upon any Third Party consents and approvals (including, without limitation, any Third Party consents or approvals required under any Permitted Encumbrance and any Lender rights, including cure rights in respect of a Financing) required in connection with such exercise. The parties covenant and agree to co-operate with one another and use their Commercially Reasonable Efforts to obtain such consents and approvals. ARTICLE 4 REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES Each Coowner represents and warrants to the other Coowners as stated below and acknowledges that each Coowner is relying on the accuracy of each such representation and warranty in entering into this Agreement. The representations and warranties made in respect of a Coowner are made only by such Coowner and shall be deemed to apply as if made continuously throughout the term of this Agreement. 4.1 Status and Capacity of the Coowners 4.1.1 Soldier Creek is a Delaware limited liability company, and has the power and capacity to execute and deliver this Agreement and to perform its obligations under this Agreement. So long as Soldier Creek owns a Coowner’s Interest, it is an Eligible Person. 4.1.2 Irish Creek is a Delaware limited liability company, and has the power and capacity to execute and deliver this Agreement and to perform its obligations under this Agreement. So long as Irish Creek owns a Coowner’s Interest, it is an Eligible Person. 4.1.3 High Banks is a Delaware limited liability company, and has the power and capacity to execute and deliver this Agreement and to perform its obligations under this Agreement. So long as High Banks owns a Co-owner’s Interest, it is an Eligible Person. 4.2 Authorization of Agreement The execution and delivery of this Agreement has been duly and validly authorized by each of the Coowners. 4.3 Enforceability This Agreement has been duly and validly executed and delivered by each of the Coowners and is a valid and legally binding obligation of each of the Coowners enforceable against each of them in accordance with its terms, subject, as to enforcement, to bankruptcy, insolvency and other laws affecting creditors’ rights generally and to general principles of equity. ARTICLE 5 THE SHARED INTERCONNECTION FACILITIES 5.1 Intention of Coowners 5.1.1 The Coowners acknowledge that they have entered into this Agreement solely for the purpose of governing their ownership of the Shared Interconnection Facilities. 5.1.2 The Coowners agree that it is their intention to operate the Shared Interconnection Facilities as would a prudent owner of a transmission line comparable to the Shared Interconnection Facilities as at the date hereof, with such changes and improvements as are Approved by the Coowners. 5.2 Decommissioning of the Shared Interconnection Facilities 5.2.1 At the end of the later of (a) the useful life of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, or (b) if the Shared Interconnection Facilities are no longer required by any Co-owner (the “Termination of Transmission Activities”), the Co-owners shall, jointly and severally, within twelve (12) months of the Termination of Transmission Activities (the “Restoration Window”) take any and all actions required by any Law, Governmental Authority or any reasonable requirement by any leasehold or easement grantor to remediate, mothball, decommission, take down, dismantle and remove all Shared Interconnection Facilities, and access roads, as required, save and except for any materials which may lie beneath the surface of the Shared Interconnection Facilities Area, and fill up all holes caused by such removal and restore the surface of the Shared Interconnection Facilities Area to the same condition as the Shared Interconnection Facilities Area was prior to entry thereon and use thereof by the Co-owners (collectively, the “Restoration Obligations”). 5.2.2 In the first month of the five (5) - year period (the “Pre-Restoration Term”) beginning on the date that is five (5) years prior to the end of the useful life of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, the Co-owners shall, in accordance with Section 0, estimate the cost of the Restoration Obligations to be performed during the Restoration Window, using, as a working assumption, that the Restoration Obligations will be performed at the beginning of the Restoration Window (the “Restoration Amount”). In the event the Co-owners are unable to agree on a Restoration Amount by the end of such first month of such Pre-Restoration Term, the determination of the Restoration Amount shall be made by an appraiser mutually agreed upon by the Co-owners. 5.3 Metering; Line Loss; Curtailment 5.3.1 Meters. Each Co-owner covenants and agrees that it shall own, operate and maintain a revenue meter, located at or in proximity to its applicable substation, which shall (a) record the Energy produced by its Project and delivered to such substation and (b) be programmed to be remotely monitored. 5.3.2 Line Loss. Each Co-owner agrees to account for and allocate the Total Transmission Loss in accordance with the fixed loss allocation factor calculated in accordance with the methodology set out in Exhibit C hereto. Each Co-owner agrees to submit and maintain the shared transformation losses (including, without limitation, the transformation losses for applicable switching stations) and line losses for those portions of the Shared Interconnection Facilities used for the common benefit of the Projects. 5.3.3 Curtailment. The Parties acknowledge and agree to the curtailment provisions set forth in the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement. ARTICLE 6 DECISION MAKING 6.1 Eligible Co-owners For the purpose of this 0, any and all references to Co-owner or Co-owners shall be references to each such Co-owner that is an Eligible Person. 6.2 Decision-Making by Coowners The Co-owners agree that major decisions regarding construction, rebuilding, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement and removal of the Shared Interconnection Facilities, or any portion thereof, that have not otherwise been delegated to the Operator, must be unanimously decided by the Co-owners. For the avoidance of doubt, any decision (i) to remove from service permanently; (ii) to sell, transfer, assign or dispose of all or any part of the Shared Interconnection Facilities except in the ordinary course of business in instances where any disposed item is being repaired or replaced; (iii) that limits a Co-owner’s ability to generate or deliver energy from such Co-owner’s Project to the point of interconnection; or (iv) to incur or authorize the Operator to incur any indebtedness related to the Shared Interconnection Facilities that the Co-owners would be obligated to repay pursuant to this Agreement shall, in each case, require the unanimous approval of the Co-owners.
6.3 Approvals, Consents and Agreements Wherever the provisions of this Agreement require an approval of or consent or agreement to (collectively, an “Approval”) any decision, action, appointment, designation, document or plan by the Coowners, such Approval may also be given in writing signed by all of the Coowners whose Approval is required pursuant to the terms of this Agreement in lieu of there being an actual meeting of the Committee. A Coowner whose Approval is required and who has agreed that an actual meeting of the Committee is not required, shall, within 5 Business Days after the receipt of a Notice requesting an Approval, give Notice to the other Coowner either that it is giving its Approval or that it withholds its Approval. If such Coowner fails to respond in writing within 5 Business Days after receipt of a Notice requesting an Approval, such Coowner shall be deemed to have given its Approval. The Approval of a Defaulting Coowner shall not, following an Event of Default in respect of such Coowner, be required by the other Coowner for the purposes of obtaining an Approval hereunder. Nothing in this Section 0 shall derogate from the right of a Coowner to make decisions and to give Approvals in its sole, absolute, unfettered and subjective discretion. ARTICLE 7 FINANCIAL MATTERS 7.1 Funds Required for the Shared Interconnection Facilities 7.1.1 Subject to Section 0, each Coowner shall be directly responsible for paying its Coowner’s Proportion of all expenses attributable to the Shared Interconnection Facilities, provided that High Banks will be solely responsible for all O&M and other costs attributable to the Series Capacitor. It is agreed that, subject to the terms of the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement, no expenses respecting the Shared Interconnection Facilities will be incurred or paid except those that are within an Approved Budget or which have otherwise been Approved by the Coowners. 7.1.2 Each Coowner shall arrange and provide its Coowner’s Proportion of the funds required from time to time for the purposes of the Shared Interconnection Facilities within the time limitations Approved by the Coowners, including without limitation the Operating Expenses and the Construction and Development Costs, provided that High Banks will be solely responsible for all costs attributable to the Series Capacitor. 7.1.3 In the event that one or both of the Irish Creek Facility and Soldier Creek Facility incur outages as a result of the commissioning or interconnection activities of the High Banks Facility, High Banks will be responsible for reimbursing Irish Creek and Soldier Creek for all penalties, damages, charges, or costs otherwise incurred by the Irish Creek and Soldier Creek Facilities as a result of the outage(s). 7.2 Indemnities 7.2.1 Each Coowner (the “Indemnifying Coowner”) agrees with the other Coowner (each an “Indemnified Coowner”) to be responsible for the Indemnifying Coowner’s Proportion of the debts, liabilities, obligations, duties, agreements and expenses properly incurred that the Indemnifying Co-owner was legally obligated to pay and that the Indemnified Co-owner pays on behalf of the Indemnifying Co-owner (the “Liabilities”) arising from or incurred in connection with the Shared Interconnection Facilities whether present or future, provided that the Liabilities have been Approved by the Coowners or incurred pursuant to the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement. 7.2.2 The Indemnifying Coowner shall at all times indemnify and save harmless the Indemnified Coowner from any and all Liabilities to the extent of that portion of all Liabilities which it has incurred and which is in excess of such Indemnified Coowner’s Proportion of the Liabilities and which has been paid or incurred by such Indemnified Coowner. The Indemnifying Coowner shall reimburse, forthwith on demand, the Indemnified Coowner with respect to such portion. 7.2.3 The Indemnifying Coowner shall at all times indemnify and save harmless the Indemnified Coowner from any and all actions, proceedings, causes, claims, demands, costs, liability, damages and expenses of every nature or kind whatsoever arising out of the Indemnifying Coowner’s separate debts, liabilities, obligations, duties and agreements, whether present or future. 7.2.4 Notwithstanding anything contained in this Agreement, recourse with respect to any monetary obligation hereunder of an Indemnifying Coowner shall be had only as against the Coowner’s Interest of such Indemnifying Coowner in the Shared Interconnection Facilities. 7.2.5 Notwithstanding anything in this Section 0 to the contrary, any indemnity owing by a Co-owner under this Section 0 shall be fully subordinated to any Lender in respect of a Financing of such Co-owner’s Project. 7.3 Short Fall Loans 7.3.1 If a Coowner (the “Non-advancing Coowner”) does not pay any amount required to be paid by it pursuant to Sections 0, 0 or 0 hereof or as required by the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement on or before the due date for such payment, then on or before the day which is 10 Business Days following a Notice of demand for such payment by the other Coowner (the “Compliant Coowner”), the Compliant Coowner may, but need not, while the amount has not been paid by the Non-advancing Coowner, advance the amount so payable by the Non-advancing Coowner for the purpose for which it is required. 7.3.2 If a Compliant Coowner advances an amount as aforesaid (a “Contributing Coowner”) on behalf of a Non-advancing Coowner, such Contributing Coowner, in addition to any other right or remedy it may have pursuant to this Agreement, shall be entitled to give Notice thereof to the Non-advancing Coowner and the amount advanced by the Contributing Coowner shall be deemed to be a demand loan made by the Contributing Coowner to the Non-advancing Coowner, which the Contributing Coowner has advanced for and on behalf of the Non-advancing Coowner and which the Non-advancing Coowner covenants to repay with interest immediately upon demand. Such demand loan shall bear interest as between the Contributing Coowner and the Non-advancing Coowner at the Prime Rate plus 2% per annum from the date of advance to the date of repayment in full and such demand loan, with interest thereon calculated as aforesaid. 7.3.3 If the amount paid by a Contributing Coowner is for payment of an amount which is secured by the Shared Interconnection Facilities or otherwise secured, then in addition to any other right of such Contributing Coowner, such Contributing Coowner shall be subrogated to any security to which the payee of such amount may be entitled upon the Coowner’s Interest of the Non-advancing Coowner or any other security to which such payee is entitled. 7.4 Access to Records The Coowners agree that the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement and any replacement agreement relating to management of the Shared Interconnection Facilities shall include a provision permitting each Coowner reasonable access to the Operator’s records with respect to the Shared Interconnection Facilities. 7.5 Taxes The Coowners agree to pay or cause to be paid as and when the same fall due, all real property taxes, rates (including local improvements), duties and assessments or other charges of a like nature imposed, charged or levied upon the Shared Interconnection Facilities when they become due and prior to the date for imposition of penalties. 7.6 Insurance The Co-owners agree to maintain the insurance identified and set forth in the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement. ARTICLE 8 TRANSFERS OF INTEREST AND CHARGES 8.1 General 8.1.1 Except as expressly permitted pursuant to this Agreement, including pursuant to this 0, no Coowner shall sell, exchange, transfer, assign, distribute, pledge, mortgage, charge, grant a security interest in or otherwise encumber or dispose of its Coowner’s Interest (or any part thereof) or this Agreement (or any interest herein), and no agreement to do so may be made (any such sale, transfer, assignment or encumbrance or agreement to do so herein referred to as a “Disposition”) except, in each case, with the prior written consent of each of the other Coowners, which consent may be arbitrarily withheld in their sole discretion and any Disposition made otherwise shall be void as between the parties to such Disposition as well as between the Coowners. 8.1.2 If any Coowner shall at any time make a Disposition in contravention of the provisions of this Agreement, the other Coowner(s) shall, in addition to all other rights and remedies under this Agreement or at law and/or in equity, be entitled to bring an application for an order restraining and enjoining such action, and the offending party shall not plead in defense thereto that there would be an adequate remedy at law and/or in equity, it being recognized and agreed that the injury and damage resulting from such a breach would be impossible to measure monetarily. 8.2 Prohibition against Disposition Notwithstanding any provision of this Agreement, no Disposition by a Coowner may be made pursuant to this Agreement if: (a) as a result thereof, the remaining Coowner(s) would become subject to more onerous governmental controls or regulations affecting the Shared Interconnection Facilities to which the Coowners were not previously subject, except for filings with the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission necessitated by such dispositions; (b) by reason of such Disposition, the remaining Coowner(s) would become subject to additional forms of taxation to which they were not previously subject; (c) the Disposition would be prohibited by law or regulation or by the terms of any Financing completed for the benefit of the Coowner proposing to make the Disposition or by the terms of any Permitted Encumbrance or would constitute a default thereunder, in each case, unless any required approval has been obtained and is in effect; or (d) the Coowner intending to effect the Disposition is a Defaulting Coowner. 8.3 Required Disposition Notwithstanding any provision of this Agreement, in the event a Co-owner permanently ceases its operations, such Co-owner (the “Transferring Co-owner”) shall transfer the Co-owner’s Interest of the Transferring Co-owner to the other Co-owners within sixty (60) days in a tax efficient manner. 8.4 Covenant of Prospective Coowner Notwithstanding anything contained in this Agreement, no Disposition may be made unless the prospective Coowner enters into an agreement with the remaining Coowner(s) (in a form satisfactory to the remaining Co-owner(s) acting reasonably) whereby the prospective Coowner shall be bound by the obligations and entitled to the benefit of this Agreement and the other agreements affecting the Shared Interconnection Facilities contemplated by this Agreement. In the event a prospective Co-owner joins this Agreement, the ownership percentages as set forth in Section 3.1 and the definition of Pro Rata Share shall be adjusted to reflect the contract capacity and aggregate MW capacity of Additional Capacity for such prospective Co-owner. 8.5 Permitted Transfers Notwithstanding the provisions of Section 0: (a) a Coowner who is an Eligible Person shall be permitted to transfer or distribute all but not less than all of its Coowner’s Interest to another Eligible Person without the approval of the other Co-owner(s); or (b) a Co-owner may make a Disposition of all but not less than all of its Co-owner’s Interest to any Person, subject to Section 0 or to an Eligible Person. However, in the case of each of clauses (a) and (b) above, each transferee must become a party to this Agreement as contemplated by Section 0, and the Coowner that is the transferor shall be released from its obligations under this Agreement as a result of any such transfer. 8.6 Financing 8.6.1 Each Coowner and any Affiliate of such Co-owner (a “Borrowing Coowner”), will be permitted to borrow funds for, without limitation, construction and/or term financing or refinancing from a Lender, secured by its Coowner’s Interest in the Shared Interconnection Facilities and its interest in this Agreement (“Financing”). 8.6.2 The Borrowing Co-owner shall notify the other Co-owner(s) in writing of the name, address, and telephone and facsimile numbers of each Lender. Such notice shall include the names of the account managers or other representatives of the Lenders to whom all written and telephonic communications may be addressed. The Borrowing Co-owner shall promptly give the other Co-owner(s) notice of any change in such information. 8.7 Release of Transferring Coowner A Coowner who makes a Disposition, in accordance with this 0, of all of its Coowner’s Interest shall thereupon have no further rights or obligations arising hereunder after such Disposition. 8.8 Planned Decommissioning Any Co-owner may, at any time during the term hereof, discontinue operation of its Co-owner’s Project after providing the other Co-owner(s) with written notice at least three (3) months prior to the date operations will cease for such Co-owner’s Project (a “Planned Decommissioning”). ARTICLE 9 DEFAULT 9.1 Default A Coowner who is not a Defaulting Coowner shall have the right to deliver to either of the other Coowners a Notice of an Event of Default in respect of such Defaulting Coowner (a “Default Notice”) specifying in reasonable detail the Event of Default and the required cure. 9.2 Events of Default 9.2.1 “Event of Default”, with respect to a Co-owner, shall mean: (a) the existence of an Event of Insolvency in respect of such Coowner and such event shall not have been cured within any cure period described in the definition of Event of Insolvency; (b) the failure of such Coowner to make any required payment to the other Coowner pursuant this Agreement and such failure continues for 10 Business Days (or 180 days if such Co-owner is actively pursuing a cure) from the receipt of the Default Notice; (c) a breach by such Coowner under 0 and such breach continues for 30 days (or 180 days if such Co-owner is actively pursuing a cure) from the receipt of the Default Notice; (d) a breach by such Coowner in the performance of any of its financial obligations under any Financing, which entitles the Lender in such Financing to enforce any security that it holds in respect of the Shared Interconnection Facilities or such Coowner’s Interest therein, and such breach continues beyond any stipulated cure period set forth in the applicable Financing; (e) a breach by such Coowner in the performance of any of its material obligations under this Agreement, other than those provided for in clauses (b), (c) and (d) above, and such breach continues for 60 days (or 180 days if such Co-owner is actively pursuing a cure) from the receipt of the Default Notice; or (f) the decommissioning of such Co-owner’s Project, if such decommissioning is not a Planned Decommissioning, and such decommission is not cured within 60 days (or 180 days if such Co-owner is actively pursuing a cure) from the receipt of the Default Notice. 9.3 Coowners Rights Upon Event of Default 9.3.1 Upon an Event of Default, the non-defaulting Coowner shall have any and all of the following rights: (a) to bring any proceedings in the nature of specific performance, injunction or other equitable remedy, it being acknowledged by all Coowners that damages at law may be an inadequate remedy for a default, breach or threatened breach of this Agreement; (b) to bring any action at law or in equity as may be permitted in order to recover damages; and (c) to give a Notice to the Defaulting Co-owner and the Operator to disconnect the Defaulting Co-owner’s Project if such Event of Default remains uncured for a further period of 10 Business Days after receipt by the Defaulting Co-owner of such Notice to disconnect, and the Defaulting Co-owner’s Project shall be disconnected from the Shared Interconnection Facilities by the Operator at the direction of the other Co-owner for so long as such Event of Default remains uncured. 9.4 Lender Rights Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this 0, a Co-owner’s right to exercise any rights pursuant to this 0, shall remain subject to any Lender’s notice or cure rights in respect of a Financing. ARTICLE 10 NOTICES 10.1 Notices 10.1.1 All notices, demands, Approvals, agreements, offers, payments or requests (a “Notice”) provided for in this Agreement shall be in writing and sent by personal delivery, courier, facsimile or return receipt electronic mail transmission and addressed as: Co-owner: Soldier Creek Wind, LLC 700 Universe Boulevard Juno Beach, FL 33408-0428 Attention: Project Finance Group Email: Email: PROJECTFINANCE.SharedMailbox@nexteraenergy.com
Co-owner: Irish Creek Wind, LLC 700 Universe Boulevard Juno Beach, FL 33408-0428 Attention: Project Finance Group Email: PROJECTFINANCE.SharedMailbox@nexteraenergy.com
Co-owner: High Banks Wind, LLC 700 Universe Boulevard Juno Beach, FL 33408-0428 Attention: Project Finance Group Email: PROJECTFINANCE.SharedMailbox@nexteraenergy.com
10.1.2 A Notice is deemed to be delivered and received (i) if sent by personal delivery, on the date of delivery if it is a Business Day and the delivery was made prior to 4:00 p.m. (local time in the place of receipt) and otherwise on the next Business Day, (ii) if sent by same-day service courier, on the date of delivery if sent on a Business Day and delivery was made prior to 4:00 p.m. (local time in place of receipt) and otherwise on the next Business Day, (iii) if sent by overnight courier, on the next Business Day, (iv) if transmitted by facsimile, on the Business Day following the date of confirmation of transmission by the originating facsimile, or (v) if transmitted by electronic mail, on the Business Day following the date when the communication is confirmed by return receipt to have been opened by the receiving party. Any party may change its address for service from time to time by providing a Notice in accordance with the foregoing, provided that any subsequent Notice must be sent to such party at its changed address. Any element of a party’s address that is not specifically changed in a Notice will be assumed to be unchanged. ARTICLE 11 GENERAL 11.1 Notice of Adverse Claim If any Coowner receives any notice, claim or document respecting the Shared Interconnection Facilities which would adversely affect the Coowner’s Interest of the other Coowner(s), it shall forthwith deliver a copy of such notice, claim or document to the other Coowner(s). 11.2 Non-Arm’s Length Transaction Except as and to the extent specifically contemplated in this Agreement, no non-arm’s length transaction of any kind will be entered into or made with respect to the Shared Interconnection Facilities unless, prior to the time at which it is entered into or made, reference to the fact and nature of that relationship is reported to the other Coowner(s) and such agreement or other arrangement is Approved by the other Coowner(s) notwithstanding such relationship. 11.3 Gender and Number Words importing the singular include the plural and vice versa. Words importing gender include all genders. 11.4 Captions and Table of Contents The captions and table of contents contained herein are for reference only and in no way effect this Agreement. 11.5 Obligations as Covenants Each obligation of a Coowner in this Agreement, even though not expressed as a covenant, is considered for all purposes to be a covenant. 11.6 Invalidity If any covenant, obligation or agreement or part thereof or the application thereof to any person or circumstance shall, to any extent, be invalid or unenforceable, the remainder of this Agreement or the application of such covenant, obligation or agreement or part thereof to any person or circumstance other than those to which it is held invalid or unenforceable shall not be affected thereby. Each covenant, obligation and agreement in this Agreement shall be separately valid and enforceable to the fullest extent permitted by law. 11.7 Amendment of Agreement No supplement, modification, waiver or termination of this Agreement shall be binding unless executed in writing by all Coowners. 11.8 Assignment 11.8.1 Except as expressly provided in this Section 11.8, the rights under this Agreement shall not be assignable or transferable nor the duties delegable by any Party without the prior written consent of the other Parties, which consent shall not be unreasonably withheld or delayed; and nothing in this Agreement, express or implied, is intended to confer upon any person or entity, other than the Parties and their permitted successors-in-interest and permitted assignees, any rights or remedies under or by reason of this Agreement unless so stated to the contrary. Notwithstanding the foregoing: (a) Each Co-owner may grant to a Secured Party a security interest in its rights under this Agreement; provided that neither the grant of any such interest, nor the foreclosure of any such interest, shall in any way release, reduce or diminish the obligations of such Co-owner hereunder. (b) This Agreement may be assigned, with ninety (90) days prior written notice to the other Co-owners: (a) to the successor of a Co-owner, (b) to a Person acquiring all or a controlling interest in the business assets of a Co-owner, (c) to an Affiliate of a Co-owner, or (d) in connection with a sale or transfer of the Facility by a Secured Party. 11.9 Successors and Assigns Except as otherwise expressly provided herein, all of the provisions of this Agreement shall be binding upon the Coowners and their respective successors and assigns and shall inure to the benefit of and be enforceable by the Coowners and their respective successors and permitted assigns. 11.10 Force Majeure For the purposes of this Agreement, the term “Force Majeure” means any act, event, cause or condition that prevents a Party from performing its obligations (other than payment obligations) or increases such Party’s obligations under this Agreement that is beyond the affected Party’s reasonable control, and shall include, without limitation, any of the following events or occurrences: (a) acts of God, including extreme wind, ice, lightning or other storms, earthquakes, tornadoes, hurricanes, cyclones, landslides, drought, floods and washouts; (b) fires or explosions; (c) local, regional or national states of emergency; (d) strikes and other labor disputes (other than legal strikes or labor disputes by employees of (i) such Party, or (ii) a Third Party contractor of such Party, unless, in either such case, such strikes or other labor disputes are the result or part of a general industry strike or labor dispute); (e) delays or disruptions (including those arising from events of Force Majeure referred to in this Section 0) in the construction of any assets that are required for the Shared Interconnection Facilities to deliver electricity; (f) civil disobedience or disturbances, war (whether declared or not), acts of sabotage, blockades, insurrections, terrorism, revolution, riots or epidemics; (g) an order, judgment, legislation, ruling or direction by Governmental Authorities restraining a Party, provided that the affected Party has not applied for or assisted in the application for and has used Commercially Reasonable Efforts to oppose said order, judgment, legislation, ruling or direction; (h) any inability to obtain, or to secure the renewal or amendment of, any permit, certificate, impact assessment, license or approval of any Governmental Authority required to perform or comply with any obligation under this Agreement, unless the revocation or modification of any such necessary permit, certificate, impact assessment, license or approval was caused by the violation of the terms thereof or consented to by the Party invoking Force Majeure; and (i) any unanticipated maintenance or outage affecting the Shared Interconnection Facilities which results directly from, or is scheduled or planned directly as a consequence of, an event of Force Majeure. 11.11 Excused Performance Except for the obligation to make payments due hereunder, any Party shall be excused from performance and shall not be considered to be in default in respect to any obligation hereunder, to the extent its performance of such obligation shall have been prevented by Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable. In the event of any Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable, such Party shall promptly notify the other Parties thereof and, so long as such condition shall persist, such Party shall not be liable for the delay in performance of, or the failure to perform, its obligations (other than obligations for payment of amounts due hereunder) under this Agreement caused directly or indirectly thereby. 11.12 Notice and Mitigation of Force Majeure and Change in Law The Party claiming a Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable, shall give the other Parties notice describing the particulars of the Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable. Within fifteen (15) days after giving notice of the Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable, the claiming Party shall give the other Parties an estimate of the expected duration and probable impact of the Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable. The claiming Party shall continue to furnish the other Parties with timely regular reports during the continuation of the Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable. Each Party shall immediately and continuously exercise reasonable efforts to mitigate or limit the impact to its obligations hereunder as a result of the Force Majeure or Change in Law, as applicable. 11.13 Accounting Principles Except as specifically provided otherwise in this Agreement, all calculations referred to herein shall be made in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles and practices applied on a consistent basis. 11.14 Time Time shall be of the essence of this Agreement, except as specifically provided otherwise in this Agreement. 11.15 Business Day Whenever, under this Agreement, any payment shall be due, any period of time would begin or end, any calculation is to be made or any other action is to be taken on or as of a day which is not a Business Day, such payment shall be made, such period of time shall begin or end, such calculation shall be made and such other action shall be taken, as the case may be, on or as of the next succeeding Business Day. 11.16 Waiver None of the provisions of this Agreement shall be considered waived by a Party unless such waiver is in writing and signed by such Party. No waiver shall be construed as a modification of any of the provisions of this Agreement or as a waiver of any default (present or future) hereunder or breach hereof, except as expressly stated in such waiver. 11.17 Rights of Coowners Independent The rights available to each Coowner under this Agreement and at law shall be deemed to be several and not dependent on each other and each such right shall be accordingly construed as complete in itself and not by reference to any other such right. Any one or more and/or any combination of such rights may be exercised by a Coowner from time to time and no such exercise shall exhaust the rights or preclude any other Coowner from exercising any one or more of such rights or combination thereof from time to time thereafter or simultaneously. 11.18 Status Reports Each Coowner agrees, upon the reasonable request of the other Coowner(s), made from time to time, to furnish promptly a written statement of any matter pertaining to the requesting Coowner to the best of the knowledge and belief of the Coowner making such statement. 11.19 Further Assurances If any Party reasonably determines that any further instruments or any other acts are necessary or desirable to carry out the terms of this Agreement, the other Parties will execute and deliver all such instruments and assurances and do all such things as the first Party reasonably deems necessary or desirable to carry out the terms of this Agreement (at the cost of the first Party). 11.20 Remedies Cumulative The rights and remedies under this Agreement are cumulative and in addition to and not in substitution for any other rights and remedies available at law or in equity or otherwise. No single or partial exercise by a party of any right or remedy precludes or otherwise affects the exercise of any other right or remedy to which that party may be entitled. 11.21 Governing Law This Agreement shall be construed and enforced in accordance with the laws of the State of Kansas without regard to its conflict of laws principles. 11.22 Dispute Resolution The Parties will attempt in good faith to promptly resolve any dispute arising out of or relating to this Agreement by use of the following procedures, in the order listed: (a) If any dispute or controversy prove incapable of being settled by the representatives of the Parties normally responsible for administration of this Agreement, such dispute shall then be sought to be resolved by negotiations between designated senior executives of the Parties who have authority to settle the controversy. (b) If the senior executives are unable to resolve a dispute arising out of this Agreement, the Parties may, by mutual written agreement, submit the dispute to arbitration. Each Party shall submit a written statement detailing the nature of the dispute, designating the issue(s) to be arbitrated, identifying the provisions of this Agreement under which the dispute arose, and setting forth such Party’s proposed resolution of such dispute. Within ten (10) days of the date the Parties’ written agreement to submit a dispute to arbitration, a representative of each Party shall meet for purpose of selecting an arbitrator. Any arbitration proceeding shall be conducted in accordance with the commercial arbitration rules of the American Arbitration Association in effect on the date of the notice. The arbitrator shall be bound by the provisions of this Agreement where applicable, and shall have no authority to modify any terms and conditions of this Agreement in any manner. Unless otherwise agreed to by the Parties, the arbitrator shall render a decision within forty-five (45) days of the conclusion of the arbitration hearing, and shall notify the Parties in writing of such decision and the reasons supporting such decision. The arbitrator shall have no authority to award any damages inconsistent with the terms of this Agreement. The fees and expenses of the arbitrator shall be shared equally by the Parties, unless the arbitrator specifies a different allocation. All other expenses and costs of the arbitration proceeding shall be the responsibility of the Party incurring such expenses and costs. The existence, contents or results of any arbitration proceeding under this Agreement may not be disclosed without the prior written consent of all Parties; provided, however, that any Party may make disclosures as may be required to fulfill regulatory obligations to any agencies having jurisdiction. Unless otherwise agreed by the Parties, any arbitration proceedings shall be conducted in Palm Beach, Florida. Any arbitral award issued in accordance with this Section shall be conclusive and binding on each Party. 11.23 Confidentiality and Public Announcements 11.23.1 Non-Disclosure. Each Party agrees to hold in confidence any information imparted to it by the other Party which pertains to Co-owners’ or Operator’s business activity in any manner, and which is not the subject of general public knowledge, including, without limitation, proprietary processes, technical information and know-how, information concerning the Co-owners’ other projects, management policies, economic policies, financial and other data and the like. This obligation shall continue to remain in full force and effect during the Term of this Agreement and for two (2) years after the date of termination or expiration of this Agreement. The preceding non-disclosure requirements shall not apply to: (a) information furnished without restriction by one Party to the other prior to the date of this Agreement; (b) information in the public domain; or (c) information obtained by one Party from a third Person not under an obligation of non-disclosure to such Party. 11.23.2 Disclosure to Government Agency. A Party may disclose any such information to the extent that such Party is required by any Government Agency to make such disclosure. If a Party becomes legally compelled to disclose any of such confidential information, such Party shall provide the other Party with prompt notice so that the other Party may seek to obtain a protective order or other appropriate remedy. In addition, the Co-owners may disclose such information to the extent that such disclosure is required by any Secured Party, Financing Agreements, any prospective Secured Party, any prospective member, independent engineer, any supplier to the Shared Interconnection Facilities and any Person providing any type of interconnection services to the Shared Interconnection Facilities, it being understood that prior to any disclosure of such information, such Persons shall be informed of the confidential nature of the information and shall agree (a) to keep the information confidential and (b) to the other terms of Article 14 of this Agreement. 11.23.3 Public Announcements. No public announcement, filing or press release concerning the Shared Interconnection Facilities, the existence of or the terms of this Agreement, the relationship between the Co-owners, or Confidential Information pertaining to the Shared Interconnection Facilities or operations thereon, will be made without the prior written consent of all Co-owners, except to the extent such public announcement or press release is required under contracts entered into with a Governmental Authority or under any Laws. 11.24 Counterparts This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts (including counterparts by facsimile, portable document format (pdf) or other electronic transmission) and all such counterparts taken together will be deemed to constitute one and the same instrument. 11.25 Whole Agreement The Coowners hereto covenant and agree that this Agreement, together with the Amended and Restated Shared Interconnection Facilities O&M Agreement, represent the entire agreement as currently constituted between all Coowners with respect to the co-ownership of the Shared Interconnection Facilities. Each Co-owner confirms that it has not entered into any oral or side agreements in respect of the subject matter of this Agreement.
